@startuml
!theme plain
title Consistency Strategy: Update DB, then Delete Cache

' === Participant Definition === '
actor "Request A" as A
actor "Request B" as B
entity "Cache" as Cache
database "Database" as DB

' === Execution Flow === '
A -> DB : Update DB to 1
B -> DB : Update DB to 2
B -> Cache : Delete cache
A -> Cache : Delete cache (this action is harmless as the key is already gone)

' === Result Annotation === '
note over A, Cache #LightGreen
**Result: DB = 2, Cache is empty.**
The next read will result in a "cache miss",
then fetch the correct data (2) from the DB and repopulate the cache.
**-> Data becomes consistent.**
end note

@enduml